{"type":"message","id":"14144b1f","parentId":"8022618b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:03:56.221Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the sessions. Excluding this cron session (e7885813):\n\n1. **agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258** - status: running, startedAt: 1776143077282 - about ~4.98 hours ago (running since ~05:04 UTC)\n2. **agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31** - status: running, startedAt: 1776152701090 - about ~2.05 hours ago (running since ~07:58 UTC)\n\n\n3. **agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134** - status: failed (pre-existing failure)\n4. **agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7** - status: running, startedAt: 1776154374281 - about ~1.74 hours ago (running since ~08:19 UTC)\n5. **agent:master-orchestrator:main** - status: done\n\nNow I'm calculating the exact durations for each session to get precise timing data.\n\nFor the Telegram group session, the runtimeMs shows it ran for about 6.7 seconds before ending at 07:32 UTC, then a new session spawned at 09:43 UTC. Looking at the 5p DTLX session from 07:58 UTC, it's been running for roughly 2 hours. The Agent Status cron session started at 10:00 UTC, about 2 minutes ago. The Cron: 5p Progress Report session started at 08:19 UTC and has been running for approximately 1 hour 43 minutes. The Telegram direct session failed after running for 6.6 seconds and hasn't restarted yet.\n\nNow I'm compiling the status report for the Lead, filtering out failed and completed sessions and calculating exact durations from the startedAt timestamps. I'm refining the duration calculations for each running session—the Telegram group has been active for about 2 hours since its last update, while the other cron jobs have been running for roughly 1.7 to 2.1 hours. I'll use these precise timings when sending the status report.","thinkingSignature":"793b9db16ccab4c7dd92e23dc0f78ba0aa8db90